# Suppress AVD-DS-0002 (Image user should not be 'root') — Postfix master must run
# as root to bind port 25 (a privileged port < 1024). Postfix uses privilege
# separation: the master spawns chroot-jailed smtpd workers that drop to the
# postfix user via setuid+chroot. Adding USER non-root at the Dockerfile level
# would prevent the master from binding port 25 and break the relay.
# CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE alone is insufficient because Postfix uses its own
# setuid model rather than the Linux capability system.
AVD-DS-0002
